  "texts": [
    "Access to CodeTutor is restricted during mid-terms and final exams, categorizing the assessment components into two groups: CodeTutor-Allowed (labs and assignments) and CodeTutor-Not-Allowed (mid-terms and final exams).",
    "This categorization facilitates an analysis of Code-Tutor's impact on student performance by examining potential dependencies on the tool and the improvement of learning outcomes in its absence.",
    "Data Analysis3.4.1 Quantitative Data Analysis.",
    "We examined the students' scores, interaction behaviors, and attitudes of using CodeTutor through multiple statistical analyses.First, we calculated descriptive statistics for all variables, including frequency with percentage for categorical variables and means and standard deviations for continuous variables.",
    "To examine the variation in students' scores before and after the intervention (i.e., the use of CodeTutor), we conducted paired-t tests for both the experimental and control groups."
